    <section id="section_lsc_hv1_1rb">
      <title>Intelligent Selection in Author Mode</title>
      <p id="p_msc_hv1_1rb"><ph keyref="product"/> supports all usual content selection methods
        using the mouse or keyboard shortcuts (for example <uicontrol><shortcut>Shift + Arrow
            Keys</shortcut></uicontrol>). When selecting content in <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol>
        mode, there may be instances where you want to select an element (along with its content)
        rather than just inline text content. There are several ways to select an element,
          including:<ul id="ul_tps_cy1_1rb">
          <li id="li_ups_cy1_1rb">You can select an element by clicking the element name in the
              <xref
              href="author-navigate-document-content.dita#author-navigate-document-content/using_the_breadcrumb_to_navigate"
                ><term>breadcrumb</term></xref>.</li>
          <li id="li_rk4_hy1_1rb">You can select an element using the <xref
              href="outliner-view.dita"><uicontrol>Outline</uicontrol> view</xref>.</li>
          <li id="li_fzg_my1_1rb">If you have the <xref
              href="author-display-markup.dita#author-display-markup/section_r1x_nv1_1rb"
                  ><uicontrol><image href="../img/TagsDrop.png" id="image_pmr_mhm_1s"/>Tags Display
                Mode</uicontrol></xref> set to any of the modes other than <uicontrol><image
                href="../img/PartialTags16.png"/>Partial Tags</uicontrol> or <uicontrol><image
                href="../img/NoTags16.png"/>No Tags</uicontrol>, you can select an element directly
            in the main editing pane by clicking on the element's tag.</li>
          <li id="li_qkd_ry1_1rb">If you have the <xref
              href="author-display-markup.dita#author-display-markup/section_r1x_nv1_1rb"
                  ><uicontrol><image href="../img/TagsDrop.png"/>Tags Display
              Mode</uicontrol></xref> set to <uicontrol><image href="../img/PartialTags16.png"
              />Partial Tags</uicontrol> (and the <xref
              href="preferences-author.dita#preferences-author/dlentry_hr4_bgk_54b"
                ><uicontrol>Compact tag layout</uicontrol> option is enabled in the
                <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> preferences page</xref>), you can still select certain
            block elements directly in the main editing pane by spanning the selection to the right
            of the end of the content that is inside a block element so that the selection includes
            the element's <i>invisible</i> end tag. In this mode, the end tag is normally not
            visible, but when your selection includes the invisible end tag, a tooltip displays the
            selected element name and the selection includes the whole element (along with its
            content). </li>
        </ul></p>
